snippet.textDisplay:
TRIGGER WARNING ⚠️
On August 9, 2018 (my birthday) I took a handful of pills, I slit my wrists and I went into my closet with an extension chord. I wrapped it around my neck and I tied the other end to the top rack. As I sat down and began losing consciousness, I asked God that if he gave me a sign that someone, ANYONE, cared about me, that I wouldn’t go through with it. That I would give life one more chance. At that very second, my phone (which I’d typed my suicide note on) rang. It was a minister from my church calling to tell me he loved me and he was thinking of me.

It’s been a year, 6 months and 4 days since I realized I have everything to love for. I’m currently undergoing intensive chemotherapy but I’ve been blessed with a beautiful baby boy who’s a daily reminder of my second chance. I have a purpose.

If you’re hurting, please, have HOPE.
Hold On, Pain Ends 💚
